HEADWORD: Tarente
<hw>Ta*ren"te</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>tarente</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A harmless lizard of
the Gecko family (<spn>Platydactylus Mauritianicus</spn>) found in
Southern Europe and adjacent countries, especially among old walls and
ruins.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

